```json
{
  "summary": "Add a filter-aware task count summary bar to the single-file HTML todo app that updates in real-time as tasks are added, completed, or deleted.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "title": "Add summary bar HTML element and CSS",
      "description": "Insert a <div id=\"summary-bar\"> element between the task list and the bottom of .container. Add CSS styles: muted text color (#888), small font size (~0.85rem), centered, padding above, and ensure it remains visible on mobile viewports without scrolling."
    },
    {
      "title": "Implement filter-aware renderSummary() function",
      "description": "Add a renderSummary() function that computes counts from the global tasks array (not filteredTasks): activeCount = tasks where !completed, completedCount = tasks where completed. Output text based on currentFilter: 'all' → 'X remaining · Y completed'; 'active' → 'X active tasks'; 'completed' → 'Y completed tasks'. When tasks.length === 0, show 'No tasks yet — add one above!' instead of counts."
    },
    {
      "title": "Wire renderSummary() into render() and update empty-msg text",
      "description": "Call renderSummary() at the end of the render() function so the bar updates on every state change. Update the #empty-msg text to be context-aware: when tasks.length === 0 show 'No tasks yet — add one above!'; when filtered view is empty but tasks exist show 'No tasks here.' (existing behavior)."
    }
  ]
}
```
